data.name: Label_FolDist.ToolTip
data.value:
Affects the draw distance of foliage (trees/bushes/etc). This setting has a performance impact especially when on the world map. Low-end PC users should use a value between 1.00-2.00.
This configurator allows a value of up to 10.00, but should not exceed 5.00.

data.name: Label_ShadDist.ToolTip
data.value:
Affects the draw distance of rendered shadows. This setting has a very large performance impact especially when on the world map. Low-end PC users should use a value between 1.00-2.00.
This configurator allows a value of up to 10.00, but should not exceed 5.00.

data.name: Label_ViewDist.ToolTip
data.value:
Affects the distance of 3D objects and environments. This setting has a large performance impact especially when on the world map. Low-end PC users should use a value between 1.00-2.00.
This configurator allows a value of up to 10.00, but should not exceed 5.00.

data.name: Label_Tonemap.ToolTip
data.value:
This is a tricky option to explain as it affects multiple effects. Use a value of 5 to enable all effects or 0 to disable.
0: Disable all effects. 1: Enable film contrast. 2: Also enable vignette. 3: Also enable film shadow tint. 4: Also enable film grain. 5: Also enable grain jitter.
Each value also enables all preceding options. May affect other options.

data.name: StripItem_DeleteINI.ToolTipText
data.value:
Deletes the Engine.ini file. This configurator requires this file so it must be created before any of the options can be configured.
Use this option if you no longer wish to apply manual settings.

data.name: StripItem_EditINI.ToolTipText
data.value:
Open the Engine.ini file in the default text editor currently set in Windows.
Note: This removes the read-only flag from the INI file. You must manually set it or reload/save it in this program.

data.name: RichTextBox_AddOptions.Text
data.value: Copy and paste multiple lines of "Engine.ini" options and values here and click "Parse" to import them into the options above. Any potential duplicate entries will be automatically excluded. When saving the INI, all options and values above will also be written to the INI file.

data.name: GridView_Options.ToolTip
data.value: Allows entering and editing advanced Unreal engine variables and values. Do note that this is at your own risk as this configurator does little verification on these settings and values. Meaning it's very posible to enter invalid settings.
